    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="318"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d318">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.CC/6–2645</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Secretary of the Interior</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_IHL1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ickes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Chairman of the United States
                        Delegation</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SERJ1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stettinius</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-26">June 26,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I have received a letter from
                    Acting Secretary <persName corresp="#p_GJC1">Grew</persName>, dated June 22,
                    transmitting the text of a telegram for me which you sent to the Acting
                        Secretary.<note n="17" xml:id="d318fn1">Message of June 22 from Secretary
                            <persName corresp="#p_SERJ1">Stettinius</persName> to Secretary
                            <persName corresp="#p_IHL1">Ickes</persName> informed him of the latest
                        developments with respect to a declaration of general policy respecting
                        dependent territories and indicated that the Committee on Trusteeship had
                        approved a revised section A which covered the points Secretary <persName
                            corresp="#p_IHL1">Ickes</persName> had raised (800.014/6–1245). For text
                        of Secretary <persName corresp="#p_IHL1">Ickes</persName>’ message of June
                        8, see minutes of meeting of the United States delegation, June 8, 9:02
                        a.m., <ref target="#pg_1197">p. 1197</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>On the basis of the language of the Trusteeship chapter which you quote, and on
                    the basis of the information which Under Secretary <persName corresp="#p_FA1"
                        >Fortas</persName> has given me, it seems to me that you have indeed been
                    able to take a very significant step forward.</p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_IHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harold L. Ickes</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
